mination on the record after an opportunity for a hearing” for consistency in the revised title. The words “in accordance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s554"},"text":"section 554 of title 5","children":[],"tail":"” are omitted for consistency and because 5:554 applies to a hearing on the record unless otherwise stated. In clause (1), the words “and a proposed transferee of a license” are omitted as being included in “applicant”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “to issue, transfer, deny the issuance or transfer of, suspend, revoke, or modify a license or to terminate, prohibit, or suspend any launch or operation of a launch site licensed by the Secretary or to prevent the launch of a payload” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idebfd73f9-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idebfd73fa-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(L), successively renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s70110"},"text":"section 70110 of title 49","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t51/s70110"},"text":"section 70110 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/5/M"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(5)(M)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 50905(a) or 50906” for “section 70105(a) or 70105a”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/5/N"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(5)(N)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 50904(c)” for “section 70104(c)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/5/O"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(5)(O)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 50908(b) or (c)” for “section 70107(b) or (c)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/5/P"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(5)(P)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 50909(a)” for “section 70108(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/492"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–492","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or 70105a” after “70105(a)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (a)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(10)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or reentry” after “prevent the launch”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(3)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/10/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(10)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or reentry site, or reentry of a reentry vehicle,” after “operation of a launch site”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
